---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL = "/api/checkout/session?dataset=classifications";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Classifications Bundle — NOGA + NACE + ISIC | openswissdata"
  description="5 economic activity classifications (NOGA 2008/2025, NACE Rev 2/2.1, ISIC Rev 4) with 5-way cross-walks, 4 languages, in CSV/JSON/Parquet/SQL. 399 CHF one-shot."
>
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <nav class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-4">
      <a href="/" class="hover:underline">Home</a> · <a href="/bundle" class="hover:underline">All datasets</a> · <span>Classifications</span>
    </nav>

    <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between flex-wrap gap-4 mb-2">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Swiss Economic Classifications Bundle</h1>
      <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-indigo-600">CHF 399</div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">
      Five economic activity classifications unified: NOGA 2008, NOGA 2025, NACE Rev 2, NACE Rev 2.1, ISIC Rev 4. Plus 5-way cross-walks anchored on NOGA 2025 classes. FR/DE/IT/EN labels. One-shot purchase, 360 days of updates included.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-10 text-sm">
      <div class="border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="font-semibold mb-1 text-slate-900">What's inside</div>
        <div class="text-slate-600">5 nomenclatures + cross-walks · 4 languages · CSV, JSON, Parquet, SQL · ~8-12 MB total</div>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="font-semibold mb-1 text-slate-900">Updates</div>
        <div class="text-slate-600">Annual refresh + major revisions · 360 days included · renewal CHF 160/year</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">5 nomenclatures in one bundle</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
      <table class="min-w-full text-sm border border-slate-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-slate-50">
          <tr class="text-left">
            <th class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Standard</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Scope</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Publisher</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-200">Languages</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 font-semibold">NOGA 2008</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">Swiss economic activities</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">BFS</td><td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs">FR/DE/IT</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 font-semibold">NOGA 2025</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">Swiss economic activities (latest, Jan 2025)</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">BFS</td><td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs">FR/DE/IT/EN</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 font-semibold">NACE Rev 2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">EU economic activities</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">Eurostat Ramon</td><td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs">EN</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 font-semibold">NACE Rev 2.1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">EU economic activities (latest)</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">Eurostat Ramon</td><td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs">EN</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 font-semibold">ISIC Rev 4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">International economic activities</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-slate-600">UN Statistics</td><td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs">EN</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">5-way cross-walks</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      One canonical table links every classification. Example: Swiss company classified as NOGA 2025 <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">64.11</code> → NACE Rev 2.1 <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">64.11</code> → NACE Rev 2.0 <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">64.11</code> → NOGA 2008 <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">64.11</code> → ISIC Rev 4 <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">6411</code> (central banking).
    </p>

    <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-10">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Free sample — 50 rows across all 5 schemes + 20 cross-walks</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3">Try before you buy. Curated preview covering Finance + Public Administration sectors.</p>
      <a href="/samples/classifications-sample.csv" download class="text-indigo-600 font-medium hover:underline">↓ Download classifications-sample.csv</a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Who is this for?</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-700 mb-8">
      <li><strong>Data teams at Swiss banks &amp; insurers</strong> — sectoral reporting, credit risk by activity</li>
      <li><strong>ERP &amp; CRM integrators</strong> — code mapping in Bexio, SAP, Salesforce deployments</li>
      <li><strong>Swiss subsidiaries of EU groups</strong> — consolidation with parent company's NACE reporting</li>
      <li><strong>Economic consultants &amp; researchers</strong> — time-series continuity across NOGA revisions</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Why the bundle instead of each separately?</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-8">
      The cross-walks are the key value. Buying NOGA + NACE + ISIC separately from public sources and building the bridge table yourself takes 40-80 hours of ETL work. At CHF 120/hour of engineering time that's CHF 4 800 - 9 600. <strong>CHF 399 for the complete, maintained bundle.</strong>
    </p>

    <div class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-10 mt-10 text-center">
      <a href={STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL} class="inline-block px-10 py-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white text-lg font-semibold transition-colors">
        Buy Classifications Bundle — CHF 399
      </a>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-3">Secure checkout via Stripe · Instant download by email · 14-day refund if not downloaded</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-6">
        Or get all 3 datasets (TARES + Classifications + FINMA) in the <a href="/bundle" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline font-medium">full bundle for CHF 799</a> and save CHF 200.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
